<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<ofx:section xmlns:ofx="http://www.openfuxml.org"
             xmlns:media="http://www.openfuxml.org/media"
             xmlns:layout="http://www.openfuxml.org/layout"
             xmlns:text="http://www.openfuxml.org/text"
             xmlns:l="http://www.openfuxml.org/list"
             container="true">

    <ofx:section container="true" classifier="windows">
        <ofx:title>Windows</ofx:title>

        <ofx:paragraph lang="en" >
            First download PostgreSQL from <text:emphasis style="typewriter">http://www.enterprisedb.com/products-services-training/pgdownload#windows</text:emphasis>.
            To start the installation double click the postgresql.exe you've downloaded and a setup wizard will guide you through.
            Follow it step by step:
        </ofx:paragraph>
        <l:list>
            <l:type ordering="unordered">
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Choose the installation directory or keep the default one and press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis>
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Next choose the data directory or keep the default one, too, and press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis>
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Enter a password you want to use as superuser, press<text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis> to continue
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis>, keep portnumber, except you need to change it.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Leave locale on default amd press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis>
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis> to start the installation.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Before pressing <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Finish</text:emphasis> assure the checkbox to start "StackBuilder" is checked.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
            </l:type>
        </l:list>
    </ofx:section>

    <ofx:section container="true" classifier="windows">
        <ofx:title>StackBuilder</ofx:title>
        <ofx:paragraph lang="en">"StackBuilder" helps you to install extensions for PostgreSQL. It opens a new window, where you have to choose your PostgreSQL installation in the dropdown menu.
            Be sure the program has internet access. If you are behind a proxy enter its data after clicking on <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Proxy Server</text:emphasis>.
            Follow these steps:
        </ofx:paragraph>
        <l:list>
            <l:type ordering="unordered">
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis> to continue.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Search for the PostGIS Bundle (see figure below) and confirm with <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis>
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Press<text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis> to start the download.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis>again.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Accept the licence and press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis> in the following window.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Choose the destination directory (default: your PostgreSQL directory) and press <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Next</text:emphasis> to start the installation.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">After the installation was successful, close it by clicking on <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Close</text:emphasis>.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
                <l:item>
                    <ofx:paragraph lang="en">Return to the StackBuilder Wizard, which should be still open, and close it with <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Finish</text:emphasis>.
                    </ofx:paragraph>
                </l:item>
            </l:type>
        </l:list>
        <ofx:paragraph lang="en">During installation you will be ask to set or change some environment variables, always confirm with <text:emphasis style="typewriter">Yes</text:emphasis>.
        </ofx:paragraph>

        <media:image id="image.admin.installation.postgres.stackbuilder">
